      <methods>
        <methodStep>
          <description>
            <para>FIS measure the departure of a population to the expectation of random
                (panmitic) reproduction. It measures how much the proportion of heterozygous loci in
                a sample departs from the expectations of random union of gametes. This statistic
                take values that range from -1 (Heterozygote excess) to 1 (Heterozygote deficit).
                The test used was the Fisher exact test, as implemented in Genepop software. A
                permutation test could have also been used. </para>
          </description>
        </methodStep>
      </methods>
